Given an undirected acyclic graph with all of the vertices having at most 3 neighbours.
Please find a vertex in the tree so that after getting the vertex as root it forms a valid binary tree

//Tip - an undirected acyclic graph is a tree itself only when it is single connected component but no multiple edges.

//But while interviewing to Google, followup questions should be asked - 

Q) How many nodes possible?
Ans) 10^5

Q) Is it single connected component?
Ans) Yes

Q) Does it have multiple edges?
Ans) No

Q) Each node can have how many edges?
Ans) atmost 3

Write conclusions - 
 -> The tree with root node can have 3 children and rest other nodes can have 2 children. 
If rest nodes have 3 children, then edges will become 4, which is not staisying the constraints.

-> If root of the tree has 2 children, the problem is already solved and no need to solve remaining problem.

->If root have 3 children, then check for a child which is having 1 or 2 edges. It is a safe option to pick child with 1 edge and that would be your leaf node.

